The paper discusses a challenge and workshop focused on multimedia processing and machine learning methods for automatic audio, visual, and physiological depression and emotion analysis. This involves the use of various computer science subfields such as multimedia (cs.MM), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
